1-Navigation and File Management:

cd directory: Change directory.
ls: List files and directories.
pwd: Print the current working directory.
mkdir directory: Create a new directory.
rm file: Remove/delete a file.
rmdir directory: Remove/delete an empty directory.
cp source destination: Copy a file or directory.
mv source destination: Move/rename a file or directory.
touch file: Create an empty file.
cat file: Display the contents of a file.
less file: View the contents of a file interactively.
head file: Display the first few lines of a file.
tail file: Display the last few lines of a file.
-----------------------------------

2-File Permissions:

chmod permissions file: Change the permissions of a file or directory.
chown user:group file: Change the owner and group of a file or directory.
chgrp group file: Change the group of a file or directory.
-----------------------------------

3-Process Management:

ps: Display currently running processes.
top: Monitor system processes and resource usage.
kill process_id: Terminate a process.
killall process_name: Terminate all processes with a given name.
bg: Run a process in the background.
fg: Bring a background process to the foreground.
jobs: List current jobs/processes.
-----------------------------------

4-Input/Output and Redirection:

echo text: Print text to the console.
printf format arguments: Print formatted text.
>: Redirect output to a file (overwrite).
>>: Redirect output to a file (append).
2>: Redirect error output to a file.
&>: Redirect both output and error output to a file.
|: Pipe output of one command to another command.
grep pattern file: Search for a pattern in a file.
wc file: Count lines, words, and characters in a file.
-----------------------------------

5-System Information:

uname: Print system information.
whoami: Print the current username.
date: Print the current date and time.
cal: Display a calendar.
df: Display disk usage information.
du: Display disk usage of files and directories.
-----------------------------------

6-Networking:

ping host: Send ICMP echo requests to a host.
ifconfig: Configure and display network interfaces.
ssh user@host: Connect to a remote host via SSH.
scp source destination: Securely copy files between hosts.
wget url: Download a file from the web.
-----------------------------------

7-Compression and Archiving:

tar options archive file/dir: Create or extract tar archives.
gzip file: Compress a file (creates a .gz file).
gunzip file.gz: Decompress a compressed file.
-----------------------------------

8-User Management:

who: Display who is logged on.
whoami: Print the current username.
passwd: Change the password for the current user.
-----------------------------------

9-Help and Documentation:

man command: Display the manual page of a command.
--help or -h: Display help information for a command.
